A man has been jailed for taking part in a torture attack on a robbery victim. Five years for torture thief A man has been jailed for taking part in a torture attack on a robbery victim.Stewart Bain and an accomplice subjected Martin Gillett to the ordeal when he was visiting a friend at Larkhall.Bain, 23, of Rosemount Lane, Larkhall, and David Brown, 36, who was earlier jailed for six years, subjected the victim to violence.He was repeatedly punched on the head and body and forced to walk to a cash machine and withdraw &pound;350.Lord Stewart, who jailed Bain for five years, said: &quot;The assault was unprovoked and showed both a degree of planning and calculated cruelty.&quot; 